{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> γείτων</b>, ονος, ὁ, ἡ, <br /> <b>neighbour, borderer</b>, γείτονες ἠδὲ ἔται Μενελάου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.16, compare 9.48, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 346, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to σύνοικος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 696b; γ. τινός 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 1451, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.4; τινί [prev. work] 2.3.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ τῶν γ. or ἐκ γειτόνων <b>from</b> or <b>in the neighbourhood</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 435, etc.; οἷον ἐκ γ. φωνὴν θηρευόμενοι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 531a; λύχνον ἐκ τῶν γ. ἐνάψασθαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 1.14; ἐκ γ. τῆς πατρίδος μετοικεῖν 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 21, compare 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 10.4.12; rarely ἀπὸ γ. 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 13.84 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν γειτόνων (i.e. οἴκοις) οἰκεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Περικειρομένη” 27, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philops.” 25, etc.; τὸ χωρίον τὸ ἐν γ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 53.10: _metaphorically_, ἐν γ. εἶναι\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] to be <b>of like kind</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Icar.” 8: proverbial, μέγα γείτονι γείτων 7th c.BC: Alcman Lyricus 50, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.87. \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> as <i>adjective</i>, <b>neighbouring, bordering</b>, πόλις, πόντος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “P.” 1.32, “N.” 9.43 \">Refs</a>]; χώρα, πύλαι, ῥοαί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 67 (Lyric poetry), “Th.” 486, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 418 (Lyric poetry): with _dative_, Ἀθήναις γ. πόλις